%N A396531 First column of the triangular array with T(0, m) = binomial(2*m, m)/(m + 1) = A000108(m) and T(n, m) = T(n - 1, m + 3) - 2*T(n - 1, m + 2) + T(n - 1, m + 1).
%C A396531 The rows are generated by iterating the operator E*Delta^2, where E is the forward shift operator, E(f(m)) = f(m + 1), and Delta = E - 1 is the forward difference operator. Thus, E*Delta^2 = E*(E - 1)^2 = E^3 - 2*E^2 + E.
%C A396531 This is the Catalan analog of A395764, which applies the same operator to the factorial sequence.
%F A396531 a(n) = Sum_{j = 0..2*n} (-1)^(2*n - j)*binomial(2*n, j)*binomial(2*(n + j),n + j)/(n + j + 1) = Sum_{j = 0..2*n} (-1)^j*binomial(2*n, j)*A000108(3*n - j).
%F A396531 a(n) = (1/(2*Pi))*Integral_{x=0..4} x^n*(x - 1)^(2*n)*sqrt((4 - x)/x) dx.
